Prerequisites 
To successfully run and reproduce this project, the following 
prerequisites are required:

1. Programming Language 
• Python3.x 
Python is used as the main programming language for 
implementing the entire sentiment analysis pipeline, including 
data preprocessing, model training, and evaluation. 

2. Required Libraries 
• pandas 
Used for loading and manipulating the dataset, particularly 
for reading CSV files and handling tabular data.  
• numpy 
Provides efficient numerical operations and is used for array 
handling, random seed initialization, and prediction 
processing.  
• re (Regular Expressions) 
Used for cleaning and normalizing Arabic text by removing 
unwanted characters, symbols, and patterns.  
• torch (PyTorch) 
Serves as the deep learning framework for handling tensors, 
utilizing GPU acceleration, and running the MARBERT 
model.  
• transformers 
Used to load and work with the pre-trained MARBERT 
model and tokenizer for Arabic sentiment classification.  
• scikit-learn 
Provides tools for splitting the dataset (training/testing) and 
evaluating model performance using metrics such as 
accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score.  
• imbalanced-learn 
Used to address class imbalance in the dataset through 
techniques such as Random Oversampling.  
• matplotlib 
Used for visualizing results, including plotting graphs such as 
the confusion matrix.  
• seaborn 
Enhances data visualization by providing more informative 
and visually appealing plots, especially for the confusion 
matrix heatmap.  
3. Development Environment 
• Google Colab 
Used as the primary development environment to run the 
notebook, execute the model, and utilize GPU acceleration 
when available.  
• Internet Connection 
Required to download the pre-trained MARBERT model 
from Hugging Face.  
• GPU (Optional but Recommended) 
Speeds up model training and evaluation, especially when 
using transformer-based models.  

4. Dataset 
• Arabic Company Reviews Dataset (CSV file) 
This dataset contains real Arabic customer reviews and is 
used as the input data for training and evaluating the 
sentiment analysis model. 
• https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/fahdseddik/arabic-company-reviews 

These prerequisites ensure the correct execution of the 
complete sentiment analysis pipeline, from data preprocessing 
to model inference and evaluation. 
